
[1]rarefaction

   RAREFAC'TION, n. [See Rarefy.]

   The act or process of expanding or distending bodies, by separating the
   parts and rendering the bodies more rare or porous, by which operation
   they appear under a larger bulk, or require more room, without an
   accession of new matter; opposed to condensation; as the rarefaction of
   air.
